###  https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000000
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000000> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                      rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000001> ;
                                      rdfs:comment "Instances of Portions Of Matter whose shape is relevant for their dispostion to participate in a manufacturing process may be (subclasses of) objects that bear a 'blank role' in the context of the manufacturing process."@en ,
                                                   """Material is defined in terms of the three main perspectives that material specifications rely on: the structure of the material (\"intensive quality\"), the performance of the material (\"behavoiral material property\") and the processing the material must have undergone (\"output of some process\").

When defining specific materials/material taxonomies, these three aspects shall be taken into account in the aristotelian (\"per genus et differentiam\") as differentiation."""@en ,
                                                   "The sum of portions of matter of the same type form a portion of matter of that type."@en ;
                                      rdfs:label "Material"@de ,
                                                 "material"@en ;
                                      <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> "Portion of Material"@en ;
                                      <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A material is a portion of matter that may participate in some manufacturing process and whose shape is not relevant for its participation in the manufacturing process."@en ;
                                      <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> "true"^^xsd:boolean .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000001
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000001> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                      rdfs:subClassOf <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000040> ;
                                      rdfs:comment """It is also representing a distinct physical or conceptual part of a material or substance.

The open energy ontology OEO defines portion of matter as a subclass of object aggregate, which implies countability. Our portion is not (precisely) countable and thus bearer of intensive properties."""@en ,
                                                   """Lome explanation for portion of matter: \"What is a molecule cluster at the cellular level? Contrary to the molecular level, at the cellular level of granularity the boundary of each molecule is outside of the level of granular focus. What forms a discontinuous cluster of countable individual molecules and thus bona fide objects at the molecular level, is a continuous and non-countable molecular substance at coarser levels of
granularity. At these coarser levels, the individual molecules cannot be differentiated and demarcated anymore and the cluster as a whole possesses only fiat inner boundaries.\""""@en ;
                                      rdfs:label "portion of matter"@en ;
                                      <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A material entity that is not demarcated by any physical discontinuities. At some finer level of granularity it is an object aggregate, at some coarser level of granularity it is a fiat object part,but at this level of granularity it is neither."@en ;
                                      <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> "true"^^xsd:boolean .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000013
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000013> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                      rdfs:subClassOf [ owl:intersectionOf ( <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000033>
                                                                             [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                               owl:onProperty <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000051> ;
                                                                               owl:someValuesFrom <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000027>
                                                                             ]
                                                                           ) ;
                                                        rdf:type owl:Class
                                                      ] ;
                                      rdfs:label "parameter specification"@en ;
                                      <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A directive information entity that specifies a parameter required or produced by a workflow function, including its intended role, position, and constraints."@en ;
                                      <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001032> "https://github.com/materialdigital/core-ontology/issues/246" .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000014
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000014> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                      rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000013> ;
                                      rdfs:label "input specification"@en ;
                                      <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A parameter specification that prescribes a data item required as input for the execution of a workflow function."@en ;
                                      <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001032> "https://github.com/materialdigital/core-ontology/issues/246" .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000015
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000015> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                      rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000013> ;
                                      rdfs:label "output specification"@en ;
                                      <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A parameter specification that prescribes a data item intended to be produced as output by the execution of a workflow function."@en ;
                                      <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001032> "https://github.com/materialdigital/core-ontology/issues/246" .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000525
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000525> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                      rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000855> ;
                                      rdfs:label "Atomkraftmikroskop"@de ,
                                                 "atomic force microscope"@en ;
                                      <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A microscope that maps the surface topography of materials at the nanoscale by scanning it with a mechanical probe."@en ,
                                                                                       "Ein Mikroskop, das die Oberflächentopographie von Materialien im Nanobereich durch Abtasten mit einer mechanischen Sonde kartiert."@de ;
                                      <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050117> "AFM"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000557
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000557> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                      rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000602> ;
                                      rdfs:label "Chromatographiesystem"@de ,
                                                 "chromatography system"@en ;
                                      <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A device used for separating mixtures into individual components using a chromatographic column and a mobile phase."@en ,
                                                                                       "Ein Gerät zur Trennung von Gemischen in einzelne Komponenten unter Verwendung einer chromatographischen Säule und einer mobilen Phase."@de .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000602
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000602> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                      rdfs:subClassOf <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000030> ;
                                      rdfs:label "Gerät"@de ,
                                                 "device"@en ;
                                      <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A device is an object that is designed to perform a specific function or task involving measurement, manipulation, processing, or analysis."@en ,
                                                                                       "Ein physisches oder virtuelles Objekt, das verwendet wird, um eine bestimmte Funktion oder Aufgabe auszuführen, häufig im Zusammenhang mit der Messung, Manipulation oder Analyse von Materialien."@de ;
                                      <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> "true"^^xsd:boolean .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000603
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000603> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                      rdfs:subClassOf <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000023> ;
                                      rdfs:label "Rolle eines Gerätes"@de ,
                                                 "device role"@en ;
                                      <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Rolle, die ein Geräte inne haben kann."@de ;
                                      <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> "true"^^xsd:boolean .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000624
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000624> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                      rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000855> ;
                                      <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000119> "“Electron microscope.” Merriam-Webster.com Dictionary, Merriam-Webster, https://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/electron%20microscope. Accessed 24 Nov. 2022."@en ;
                                      rdfs:label "Elektronenmikroskop"@de ,
                                                 "electron microscope"@en ;
                                      <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A microscope that uses a beam of electrons to create high-resolution images of a sample's surface or structure."@en ,
                                                                                       "An electron-optical instrument in which a beam of electrons is used to produce an enlarged image of a minute object."@en ,
                                                                                       "Ein Gerät, das einen Elektronenstrahl verwendet, um hochauflösende Bilder der Oberfläche oder Struktur einer Probe zu erstellen."@de .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000657
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000657> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                      rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000557> ;
                                      rdfs:label "Gaschromatographiesystem"@de ,
                                                 "gas chromatography system"@en ;
                                      <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A chromatography system used for separating and analyzing compounds in a gas mixture using a chromatographic column."@en ,
                                                                                       "Ein Chromatographiesystem zur Trennung und Analyse von Verbindungen in einem Gasgemisch unter Verwendung einer chromatographischen Säule."@de .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000659
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000659> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                      rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000557> ;
                                      rdfs:label "Gelpermeations-Chromatographiesystem"@de ,
                                                 "gel permeation chromatography system"@en ;
                                      <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A chromatography system used for separating and analyzing polymers based on their molecular size using gel permeation chromatography."@en ,
                                                                                       "Ein Chromatographiesystem zur Trennung und Analyse von Polymeren basierend auf ihrer Molekülgröße durch Gelpermeationschromatographie."@de .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000784
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000784> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                      rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000557> ;
                                      rdfs:label "Hochleistungsflüssigkeitschromatographiesystem"@de ,
                                                 "high performance liquid chromatography system"@en ;
                                      <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A chromatography system used for separating, identifying, and quantifying compounds in liquid samples through high performance liquid chromatography."@en ,
                                                                                       "Ein Chromatographiesystem zur Trennung, Identifizierung und Quantifizierung von Verbindungen in Flüssigkeitsproben durch Hochleistungsflüssigkeitschromatographie."@de .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000785
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000785> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                      rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000657> ;
                                      rdfs:label "Hochtemperatur-Gaschromatographiesystem"@de ,
                                                 "high temperature gas chromatography system"@en ;
                                      <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A gas chromatography system used for separating and analyzing compounds in a gas mixture at high temperatures using a chromatographic column."@en ,
                                                                                       "Ein Gaschromatographiesystem zur Trennung und Analyse von Verbindungen in einem Gasgemisch bei hohen Temperaturen unter Verwendung einer chromatographischen Säule."@de .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000796
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000796> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                      rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000557> ;
                                      rdfs:label "Ionenaustausch-Chromatographiesystem"@de ,
                                                 "ion exchange chromatography system"@en ;
                                      <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A chromatography system used for separating ions in a sample using ion exchange resins in a chromatographic column."@en ,
                                                                                       "Ein Chromatographiesystem zur Trennung von Ionen in einer Probe unter Verwendung von Ionenaustauschharzen in einer chromatographischen Säule."@de .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000797
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000797> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                      rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000855> ;
                                      rdfs:label "Ionenmikroskop"@de ,
                                                 "ion microscope"@en ;
                                      <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A microscope that uses ions to create high-resolution images of the surface or structure of a sample."@en ,
                                                                                       "Ein Mikroskop, das Ionen verwendet, um hochauflösende Bilder der Oberfläche oder Struktur einer Probe zu erstellen."@de .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000835
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000835> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                      rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000602> ;
                                      rdfs:label "Massenspektrometer"@de ,
                                                 "mass spectrometer"@en ;
                                      <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A device used to measure the mass-to-charge ratio of ions to identify and quantify compounds in a sample."@en ,
                                                                                       "Ein Gerät zur Messung des Massen-zu-Ladung-Verhältnisses von Ionen zur Identifizierung und Quantifizierung von Verbindungen in einer Probe."@de .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000855
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000855> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                      rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000602> ;
                                      rdfs:label "Mikroskop"@de ,
                                                 "microscope"@en ;
                                      <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A device used to magnify and view small objects or details that are not visible to the naked eye."@en ,
                                                                                       "Ein Gerät zur Vergrößerung und Betrachtung kleiner Objekte oder Details, die mit bloßem Auge nicht sichtbar sind."@de .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000874
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000874> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                      rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000855> ;
                                      rdfs:label "Optisches Mikroskop"@de ,
                                                 "optical microscope"@en ;
                                      <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A microscope that uses visible light and lenses to magnify and view small objects or details."@en ,
                                                                                       "Ein Mikroskop, das sichtbares Licht und Linsen verwendet, um kleine Objekte oder Details zu vergrößern und zu betrachten."@de .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000888
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000888> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                      owl:equivalentClass [ owl:intersectionOf ( <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000000>
                                                                                 [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                   owl:onProperty <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002353> ;
                                                                                   owl:someValuesFrom <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0010033>
                                                                                 ]
                                                                               ) ;
                                                            rdf:type owl:Class
                                                          ] ;
                                      rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000000> ,
                                                      [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                        owl:onProperty <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002353> ;
                                                        owl:someValuesFrom <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0010033>
                                                      ] ;
                                      <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000116> "Classified by morphology."@en ;
                                      rdfs:label "polymer"@en ;
                                      <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A polymer is an engineered material that consists of many repeated subunits (monomers) to form long chains. The atoms within a polymer chain are bonded together by covalent bonds. The intermolecular forces between polymer chains are typically represented by van der waals forces and hydrogen bonds."@en ;
                                      <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> "true"^^xsd:boolean .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000890
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000890> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                      rdfs:subClassOf <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000027> ;
                                      rdfs:label "connected material entity aggregate"@en ;
                                      <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "An object aggregate that is a mereological sum of separate material entities, which adhere to one another through chemical bonds or physical junctions that go beyond gravity."@en ;
                                      <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> "the atoms of a molecule, the molecules forming the membrane of a cell, the epidermis in a human body"@en ;
                                      <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> "true"^^xsd:boolean .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000891
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000891> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                      rdfs:subClassOf <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000027> ;
                                      rdfs:label "disconnected material entity aggregate"@en ;
                                      <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "An object aggregate that is a mereological sum of scattered (i.e. spatially separated) material entities, which do not adhere to one another through chemical bonds or physical junctions but, instead, relate to one another merely on grounds of metric proximity. The material entities are separated from one another through space or through other material entities that do not belong to the group."@en ;
                                      <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> "a heap of stones, a colony of honeybees, a group of synapses, the trees of a forest, the canopy of a forest, the fish of a shoal, a group of commuters on the subway, the patients in a hospital"@en ;
                                      <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> "true"^^xsd:boolean .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000893
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000893> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                      rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000891> ;
                                      rdfs:label "powder"@en ;
                                      <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A powder is a dry, solid disconnected material entity aggregate composed of many very fine particles. These particles can flow freely when shaken or tilted."@en ;
                                      <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> "true"^^xsd:boolean .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000922
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000922> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                      rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000624> ;
                                      rdfs:label "Rasterelektronenmikroskop"@de ,
                                                 "scanning electron microscope"@en ;
                                      <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A scanning electron microscope (SEM) is a measuring device that produces high-resolution images of a sample surface by scanning it with a focused beam of electrons."@en ,
                                                                                       "Ein Rasterelektronenmikroskop (REM) ist ein Messgerät, das hochauflösende Bilder einer Probenoberfläche erzeugt, indem es sie mit einem fokussierten Elektronenstrahl abtastet."@de .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000963
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000963> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                      rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000557> ;
                                      rdfs:label "supercritical fluid chromatography system"@en ,
                                                 "Überkritisches Fluid-Chromatographiesystem"@de ;
                                      <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A chromatography system for separating and analyzing compounds using supercritical fluids as the mobile phase in chromatography."@en ,
                                                                                       "Ein Chromatographiesystem zur Trennung und Analyse von Verbindungen unter Verwendung überkritischer Flüssigkeiten als mobile Phase in der Chromatographie."@de .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000990
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000990> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                      rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000557> ;
                                      rdfs:label "Dünnschichtchromatographiesystem"@de ,
                                                 "thin layer chromatography system"@en ;
                                      <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A chromatography system used for separating compounds in a sample using a thin layer of adsorbent material on a plate."@en ,
                                                                                       "Ein Chromatographiesystem zur Trennung von Verbindungen in einer Probe unter Verwendung einer dünnen Schicht adsorbierenden Materials auf einer Platte."@de .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0010033
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0010033> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                      rdfs:subClassOf <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000015> ;
                                      rdfs:label "polymerization"@en ;
                                      <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "The chemical process of reacting monomers, oligomers, or reactive precursors together to form longer macromolecular chains or three-dimensional networks"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0010034
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0010034> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                      rdfs:subClassOf <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000015> ;
                                      rdfs:label "curing"@en ;
                                      <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "The toughening or hardening of a polymer material by cross-linking of polymer chains."@en .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020115
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020115> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                      rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000891> ;
                                      rdfs:label "aerosol"@en ;
                                      <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> """An aerosol is a disconnected material entity aggregate which:
1. consists of some portion of matter whose aggregate state quality concretizes gaseous and 
2. consists of some portion of matter whose aggregate state quality concretises solid or liquid (TODO: express that this portion is also a disconnected material entity aggregate)"""@en ;
                                      <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> "true"^^xsd:boolean .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020126
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020126> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                      rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000890> ;
                                      <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000119> """old defintion: A foam is a material entity aggregate that is also a composite material c. 
The parts of c that have the filler role are vacuum-filled or gas filled pores. 
The parts of c that have the matrix role consist of a material that is bearer of solid or liquid aggregate state. 
One pore with its surrounding matrix is called 'cell'. 
Depending on the interconnectedness of the pores the foam is open- or closed-cell.""" ;
                                      rdfs:label "foam"@en ;
                                      <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A foam is a connected material entity aggregate that consists of a solid or liquid matrix containing gas-filled or vacuum-filled pores forming cellular structures."@en ;
                                      <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> "true"^^xsd:boolean .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025008
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025008> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                      rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000624> ;
                                      rdfs:label "Transmissionselektronenmikroskop"@de ,
                                                 "transmission electron microscope"@en ;
                                      <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "An electron microscope that produces high-resolution images of a sample's internal structure by transmitting electrons through the sample."@en ,
                                                                                       "Ein Elektronenmikroskop, das hochauflösende Bilder der inneren Struktur einer Probe erzeugt, indem es Elektronen durch die Probe strahlt."@de ;
                                      <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050117> "TEM" .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050004
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050004> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                      rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000888> ;
                                      rdfs:label "thermoplastic polymer"@en ;
                                      <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "polymer that becomes moldable when heated and solidifies upon cooling"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050006
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050006> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                      rdfs:label "low-density polyethylene"@en ;
                                      <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "polyethylene that is characterized by a branched molecular structure and low density"@en ;
                                      <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050117> "PE-LD" .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050007
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050007> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                      rdfs:label "high-density polyethylene"@en ;
                                      <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "polyethylene that is characterized by a linear molecular structure and high density"@en ;
                                      <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050117> "PE-HD" .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050008
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050008> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                      rdfs:label "linear low-density polyethylene"@en ;
                                      <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "polyethylene that is distinguished by its linear backbone with short-chain branching"@en ;
                                      <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050117> "PE_LLD" .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050009
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050009> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                      rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050004> ;
                                      rdfs:label "polypropylene"@en ;
                                      <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> "polyethene" ;
                                      <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#comment> "this excludes ultra hight molecular polyethylen because very high molecular weight polyethylene is not thermoplastic anymore" ;
                                      <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "thermoplastic polymer produced by polymerization of the monomer propylene including further crosslinking and modifications using other comonomers"@en ;
                                      <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050117> "PP" .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050010
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050010> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                      rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050009> ;
                                      rdfs:label "isotactic polypropylene"@en ;
                                      <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "polypropylene in which all the methyl groups are aligned on the same side of the polymer chain"@en ;
                                      <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050117> "iPP" .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050011
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050011> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                      rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050009> ;
                                      rdfs:label "syndiotactic polypropylene"@en ;
                                      <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "polypropylene in which the methyl groups alternate regularly along the polymer chain"@en ;
                                      <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050117> "sPP" .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050012
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050012> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                      rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050009> ;
                                      rdfs:label "atactic polypropylene"@en ;
                                      <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "polypropylene in which the methyl groups are randomly distributed along the polymer chain"@en ;
                                      <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050117> "aPP" .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050013
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050013> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                      rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050004> ;
                                      rdfs:label "polyvinyl chloride"@en ;
                                      <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> "vinyl or polyvinyl" ;
                                      <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#comment> "they are usualy hard or soft and flexible with incrased use of plasticisers." ;
                                      <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "thermoplastic polymer produced by polymerization of the monomer vinyl chloride"@en ;
                                      <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050117> "PVC" .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050014
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050014> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                      rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050013> ;
                                      rdfs:label "rigid polyvinyl chloride"@en ;
                                      <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "polyvinyl chloride that is characterized by its stiffness and durability"@en ;
                                      <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050117> "uPVC" .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050015
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050015> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                      rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050013> ;
                                      rdfs:label "flexible polyvinyl chloride"@en ;
                                      <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "polyvinyl chloride that has been modified with plasticizers to impart flexibility"@en ;
                                      <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050117> "fPVC" .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050016
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050016> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                      rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050004> ;
                                      rdfs:label "polystyrene"@en ;
                                      <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "thermoplastic polymer produced by polymerization of the aromatic hydrocarbon styrene"@en ;
                                      <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050117> "PS" .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050017
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050017> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                      rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050016> ;
                                      rdfs:label "general purpose polystyrene"@en ;
                                      <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "polystyrene that is valued for its clarity and ease of processing"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050018
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050018> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                      rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050016> ;
                                      rdfs:label "high impact polystyrene"@en ;
                                      <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "polystyrene that is modified with rubber to improve its impact resistance"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050019
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050019> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                      rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050004> ;
                                      rdfs:label "polyethylene terephthalate"@en ;
                                      <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#comment> "it is the dominant polyester utilized in global packaging and fiber applications" ;
                                      <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "thermoplastic polymer produced by polycondensation of ethylene glycol and terephthalate precursors"@en ;
                                      <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050117> "PET" .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050020
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050020> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                      rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050019> ;
                                      rdfs:label "amorphous polyethylene terephthalate"@en ;
                                      <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "polyethylene terephthalate that is characterized by a non-crystalline structure"@en ;
                                      <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050117> "APET" .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050021
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050021> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                      rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050019> ;
                                      rdfs:label "crystalline polyethylene terephthalate"@en ;
                                      <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "polyethylene terephthalate that is distinguished by its ordered, crystalline structure"@en ;
                                      <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050117> "CPET" .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050022
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050022> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                      rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000888> ,
                                                      [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                        owl:onProperty <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002353> ;
                                                        owl:someValuesFrom <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0010034>
                                                      ] ;
                                      rdfs:label "thermosetting polymer"@en ;
                                      <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "polymer that, once cured, irreversibly sets into a permanent shape"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050023
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050023> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                      rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050022> ;
                                      rdfs:label "epoxy resin"@en ;
